    <stitle>ANTILOCK RELAY VALVE: AR-1 - DESCRIPTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>The AR-1 Antilock Relay valve is a specialized service brake relay valve. It is essentially an R-14
                relay valve with a special cover that permits direct attachment of an antilock Controller, such as the
                EC-15 (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0402601">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                ). When combined with an antilock controller, the resulting assembly is referred to as a CR-15 Antilock
                Controller/Relay. For example, when the AR-1 Antilock Relay valve is combined with the EC-15 Tractor
                Antilock Controller, the resulting assembly is referred to as a CR-15 AntiLock Controller\Relay. While
                intended for use on antilock-equipped vehicles, the AR-1 AntiLock Relay Valve functions solely as a
                service brake relay and contains no electronics of its own (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0402602">Figure 2</hotlnk>
                ).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0402601" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0402601" filename="../figg04/g0402601.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. CR 15 (Cross Section AR 1 Relay Valve)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. EC-15 CONTROLLER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. R-14 RELAY VALVE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0402602" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0402602" filename="../figg04/g0402602.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. AR 1 Relay Valve</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>In an air brake system, the AR-1 serves as a relay station to speed the application and release of the
                service brakes. The valve is normally mounted close to the service antilock modulators it serves. A
                mounting bracket furnished with the valve permits either frame or crossmember mounting. All air
                connections on the AR-1 are identified with cast, embossed letters for ease of installation. The letter
                identification and air line connections are shown in Table 1 for reference.
            </para>
            <para>Like the R-14 relay valve, the AR-1 incorporates a quick release valve next to the service port, which
                provides for rapid exhaust of control air pressure from above the relay piston. The standard AR-1 is
                offered with a 4 psi crack pressure.
            </para>
            <para>The AR-1 internal components are interchangeable with the R-12 and R-14 relay valves, therefore, the
                same maintenance kit is used to service all three valves.
            </para>
